[33.259, "o", "\r\n\u001b[38;2;142;68;207m\u001b[1m  в”Ғв”Ғ CLAUDE SYNTHESIS в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғ\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "    BRCA1 encodes a 1863-aa tumor suppressor that functions as the central scaffold for homologous recombination (HR) repair of DNA double-strand breaks. Its RING domain (residues 1вҖ“109) heterodimerizes with BARD1 to form an E3 ubiquitin ligase, while the tandem BRCT domains (1646вҖ“1859) read phospho-SXXF motifs on Abraxas, BACH1/FANCJ, and CtIP to assemble the A, B, and C complexes that govern 5вҖІ end resection, RAD51 loading, and S/G2 checkpoint control. Loss of BRCA1 forces cells onto error-prone NHEJ and microhomology-mediated end joining, producing the hallmark genomic scar вҖ” COSMIC mutational signature 3, large-scale tandem duplications, and chromosomal instability. The 125 kb locus on 17q21.31 generates 47 transcripts, but the canonical full-length isoform is the HR-competent species; the О”11q splice variant (lacking exon 11) is HR-deficient and accumulates in tumors under PARPi pressure as a reversion mechanism.\r\n    Clinically, BRCA1 is the highest-penetrance breast and ovarian cancer gene kno"]
[0.000, "o", "wn. Germline pathogenic variants confer ~65вҖ“72% lifetime breast cancer risk and ~40вҖ“44% ovarian cancer risk, with founder alleles 185delAG and 5382insC accounting for the bulk of Ashkenazi Jewish cases. Pathogenic variation clusters in two regions: truncating frameshift/nonsense mutations across the gene (NMD-targeted, complete LoF) and missense variants concentrated in the RING and BRCT domains where they disrupt fold stability or phospho-peptide binding (C61G, M1775R, R1699W). Somatic BRCA1 promoter hypermethylation phenocopies germline loss in ~10вҖ“15% of triple-negative breast cancers and high-grade serous ovarian carcinomas, expanding the HR-deficient population beyond carriers.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    Therapeutically, BRCA1 loss is a synthetic lethal target for PARP inhibitors (olaparib, rucaparib, niraparib, talazoparib), all FDA-approved in BRCA-mutant breast, ovarian, pancreatic, and prostate cancers. Resistance is driven by secondary reversion mutations restoring the reading frame, loss of 53BP1/RIF1/Shieldin (which restores resection in BRCA1-null cells), and re-expression of hypomorphic isoforms. ATR and POLОё inhibitors are the leading second-line strategies; POLОё specifically kills the MMEJ-dependent BRCA1-null cell and is in active Phase II trials (novobiocin, ART4215). Variant interpretation remains the bottleneck вҖ” ~30% of clinical BRCA1 variants are VUS, and saturation genome editing (Findlay et al., 2018) is now the reference functional assay for ClinVar reclassification.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    Experimental recommendations: (1) For functional characterization of VUS, deploy SGE in HAP1 or hESC backgrounds with a 6-day cisplatin/camptothecin survival readout вҖ” this gives single-nucleotide-resolution function scores correlating r > 0.9 with clinical pathogenicity. (2) For HRD quantification in patient samples, combine genomic scar assays (Myriad MyChoice CDx, AmoyDx HRD Focus) with functional RAD51 foci IF on FFPE вҖ” the latter detects reversion-driven restoration that genomic scars miss. (3) For mechanistic resection studies, use END-seq or BLESS in isogenic BRCA1вҲ’/вҲ’ RPE-1 cells Вұ 53BP1 KO to map resection endpoints; pair with U-DSB-seq for break-induced replication intermediates. (4) For preclinical drug development, the standard panel is UWB1.289 (BRCA1-null ovarian) Вұ BRCA1 add-back, SUM149PT (BRCA1 5382insC TNBC), and HCC1937; supplement with BRCA1-mutant PDX (e.g., HBCx-10, OV-04) for in vivo PARPi/POLОёi combinations.\r\n    Given the 47-transcript complexity at this locus, any knock"]
[0.000, "o", "out or knockdown experiment must be validated at the isoform level вҖ” short-hairpin and CRISPRi guides targeting exon 11 spare the О”11q isoform and produce hypomorphic rather than null phenotypes, a common pitfall that confounds HR assay interpretation. Use exon-1/2 or BRCT-targeting guides for clean nulls, and confirm by RAD51 foci formation after 10 Gy IR вҖ” the gold-standard functional readout.\r\n"]
